The paper discusses a management framework for secure multiparty computation (SMC) in dynamic environments, which involves addressing issues related to node discovery, trust establishment, and robustness of SMC sessions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Machine Learning (cs.LG), as these categories are relevant to the topics discussed in the paper.
